description:
Async test patterns in codebase:

=== Tokio Test Pattern ===
#[tokio::test]
async fn test_name() {
    // async test body
}

=== SQLx Test Pattern ===
- No sqlx::test macro currently used
- Tests use in-memory fakes instead of real DB
- Integration tests use sqlite::memory:

=== Repository Test Pattern ===
#[async_trait::async_trait]
impl QuoteRepository for InMemoryQuoteRepository {
    async fn find_by_id(&self, id: &QuoteId) -> Result<Option<Quote>, RepositoryError> {
        let quotes = self.quotes.read().await;
        Ok(quotes.get(&id.0).cloned())
    }
}

=== Env Isolation Pattern ===
static ENV_LOCK: OnceLock<Mutex<()>> = OnceLock::new();
fn with_env(vars: &[(&str, &str)], test_fn: impl FnOnce()) {
    let _guard = ENV_LOCK.get_or_init(|| Mutex::new(())).lock();
    // set env vars, run test, restore vars
}

=== Async Test Best Practices ===
1. Use #[tokio::test] for async tests
2. Use RwLock<HashMap<>> for shared state
3. Use sqlite::memory: for DB tests
4. Use OnceLock<Mutex<>> for env isolation
5. Prefer in-memory fakes for unit tests
6. Use real components for integration tests

=== Files with Async Tests ===
- crates/db/src/repositories/*.rs (all use tokio)
- crates/slack/src/events.rs (tokio::test)
- crates/slack/src/commands.rs (tokio::test)
- crates/server/src/bootstrap.rs (tokio::test)
